{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"environment","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ViewEnvironment","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15ViewEnvironmentAAV"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["iOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you’d like to provide overrides for the environment as it flows through a node, you should conform to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ViewEnvironmentObserving"},{"type":"text","text":" and provide those overrides in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"customize(environment:)"},{"type":"text","text":". E.g.:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func customize(environment: inout ViewEnvironment) {","    environment.traits.mode = .dark","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default, this property gets the environment by recursively walking to the root of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"propagation path, and applying customizations on the way back down. The invalidation path may be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"interrupted if a node has set it’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"environmentAncestor"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":", even if there is a node","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which specifies this node as an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"environmentDescendant"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you’d like to update the return value of this variable and have those changes propagated through the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":